text: Molenlanden is a municipality in the province of South Holland, the Netherlands. About 44,000 people were living there in 2021. It was created from the former municipalities of Giessenlanden and Molenwaard on 1 January 2019. Molenlanden covers most part of the Alblasserwaard region. A tiny part in the southeast lies in the Vijfheerenlanden region. == References == * Plaatsengids.nl Category:2019 establishments in the Netherlands
